### Taking Care of Air Letters

One must not forget that during the period these air letters were bought, China was in turmoil. People were suffering and many had to save hard to buy these in order to communicate with their loved ones. These items are already over 60 years old and the paper constitution makes them very fragile. Store them in a album with a nice backing and protector sheets. 

### Estimates and Valuations

The figures shown, are probably on the low side. Expect to pay anything from $50 to in excess of $700.00. Given the short period of use, their fragile nature and the growing chinese philatelic market they can make a good long term investment, if you can part with them.










                                                                                                                      